Life is so slowly written,  
   It shuffles like the footfalls,  
   Intent on seizing the moments,  
   Like a night with stars unfolding.  
   In the veins of flesh and earth,  
   Beauty drifts with the fading light,  
   While the petals dance, tremble,  
   And hope sifts through the shadows.

- Frank Norris
